definition: to hand over/to deliver/to pay (money)/to turn over/to make friends/to intersect (lines)/variant of 跤[jiao1]
echo/sound/noise/to make a sound/to sound/to ring/loud/classifier for noises

sentences.english: Well go to a concert tomorrow evening to hear the symphony orchestra.
sentences.chinese: 明天晚上我们去参加音乐会，听交响乐队的演奏。

sentences.english: The trombone is an essential musical instrument for a symphony orchestra.
sentences.chinese: 拉管是交响乐队不可缺少的乐器之一。

sentences.english: The Sinfonietta shares the stage with a consort of viols.
sentences.chinese: 这支小交响乐队与一群六弦提琴师同台献艺。

sentences.english: Together with the choir and symphony orchestra of Shenzhen.
sentences.chinese: 由深圳女子学院的歌咏队伴唱，深圳交响乐队伴奏。

sentences.english: The orchestra conductor stepped up to the podium.
sentences.chinese: 交响乐队的指挥走上了指挥台。

sentences.english: Would she rather join the bowling league or the metropolitan symphony?
sentences.chinese: 她宁愿加入保龄球队或都市交响乐队吗？

definition: to perform on a musical instrument
musical ensemble of several instruments (e.g. duet 二重奏 or trio 三重奏)
part (in multi-part instrumental or choral music), such as the soprano part or bass part
double reed wind instrument (such as oboe or bassoon)
